9. Pass System

Like LLVM passes, Pantheon IR should support modular transformation passes.

9.1 Parse Pass

Turns raw input into candidate objects and relations.

Function: surface extraction

⸻

9.2 Spider Pass

Builds relationship topology.

Function: graph weaving
Output: dependency graph, analogy graph, cluster map

⸻

9.3 Mirror Pass

Checks coherence, invariants, and ethics.

Function: consistency + alignment audit
Output: contradiction list, invariant violations, ethical score update

⸻

9.4 Hound Pass

Detects anomalies, bottlenecks, hidden signals, overcompression.

Function: anomaly / scent tracking
Output: suspicion markers, missing edges, drift alerts

⸻

9.5 Raven Pass

Compresses and re-encodes into high-density representation.

Function: semantic compression
Output: summary form, symbolic encoding, prime extraction

⸻

9.6 Checksum Pass

Creates integrity hash over important structure.

Function: reproducibility + ledger fit
Output: structural fingerprint, audit seal

⸻

9.7 Conductor Pass

Routes IR into target basis.

Function: basis switch / orchestration
Targets: prose, code, image prompt, workflow, pitch, doctrine, checklist

⸻

9.8 Garcia Pass

Forces delivery.

Function: convert model to artifact/action
Output: something usable now

⸻

10. Optimization Passes

Pantheon IR should support semantic equivalents of compiler optimization.

10.1 Dead Meaning Elimination

Remove objects that do not affect action, understanding, or output.

10.2 Contradiction Folding

Detect conflicting claims and resolve or mark them.

10.3 Narrative Inlining

Expand compressed references when human clarity is needed.

10.4 Pattern Hoisting

Lift reusable structures into templates or doctrines.

10.5 Constraint Propagation

Push limits through the graph so downstream options reflect reality.

10.6 Drift Reduction

Collapse parallel but incompatible narratives unless explicitly allowed.

10.7 Reversibility Preference

Prefer branches that preserve optionality.

10.8 Prime Compression

Reduce a complex graph to irreducible invariants and operators.

