⸻

12. Fact / Inference / Symbolic Separation

Every meaningful unit should be labelable as one of:

FACT
INFERENCE
HYPOTHESIS
SYMBOLIC_FRAME
PREFERENCE
COMMAND
QUESTION

This is crucial.

Pantheon gets more powerful, not less, when it can say:
	•	this is observed
	•	this is inferred
	•	this is metaphor
	•	this is desired
	•	this is still uncertain

Without that separation, the IR muddies itself.

⸻

13. Time Semantics

Pantheon IR should encode temporal structure directly.

temporal:
  origin_time:
  valid_until:
  recurrence:
  sequence_index:
  latency:
  decay_rate:
  revision_count:

This matters because some ideas are:
	•	enduring invariants
	•	temporary states
	•	expiring constraints
	•	recurring patterns

LLVM cares about runtime.
Pantheon must care about lived time, revision time, and narrative time.

⸻

14. Uncertainty Semantics

Every object and relation should tolerate imperfect certainty.

Suggested fields:

certainty: 0.0 - 1.0
evidence_strength: 0.0 - 1.0
dispute_flag: true | false
requires_validation: true | false

Pantheon should not force false confidence.

⸻

15. Ethical and Governance Fields

Pantheon is not value-neutral by default.

Each packet should support:

governance:
  ethics_score:
  risk_level: low | moderate | high
  misuse_potential: low | moderate | high
  human_review_required: true | false
  blocked_actions: []


