17. Pantheon IR Instruction Set

If you want the LLVM flavor more strongly, you can define a small semantic instruction set.

Example ops

ASSERT          declare object or invariant
LINK            create relation
WEIGH           assign importance
TAG             assign domain tag
SCOPE           assign temporal or operational scope
SPLIT           separate fact/inference/symbolic layers
MERGE           unify equivalent structures
BLOCK           mark forbidden path
ROUTE           send object to target basis
COMPRESS        reduce to prime form
EXPAND          rehydrate for human readability
AUDIT           run integrity/governance check
EXECUTE         emit action or artifact
OBSERVE         ingest feedback
REVISE          update packet

Tiny pseudo-IR example

ASSERT o1 type=concept label="Pantheon"
ASSERT o2 type=concept label="LLVM"
ASSERT o3 type=concept label="IR"

LINK o1 analogous_to o2 weight=0.84
LINK o3 enables o1 weight=0.95

ASSERT inv1 type=invariant label="fact/inference separation"
ASSERT inv2 type=invariant label="ethics >= 0.7"

AUDIT all
ROUTE o1 target="design_spec"
EXECUTE packet="pir_cmp_llvm_001"


